Jason,

Ummm....I must have been asleep for about 10 years or something...

What? notoriously *hot* t4 engine are we discussing here??????

Moisture laden air is able to absorb more heat or cool cause it is
"thicker"....or as the physicists among us will call heat absorbtion
factor.  More molecules of water in the air means it is denser and can do
more "work" to heat or cool.

Splashing a lot of water on the bottom of the case always helps too!


Cheers, dave
